{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/pulls/519", "id": 300234059, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzAwMjM0MDU5", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/519", "diff_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/519.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/519.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/issues/519", "number": 519, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Add ParamViewer class ", "user": {"login": "lukasheinrich", "id": 2318083, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIzMTgwODM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2318083?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich", "html_url": "https://github.com/lukasheinrich", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "# Description\r\n\r\nadds a `ParamViewer` class to be used by the combined modifiers. Allows to splice out the correct subset of parameter values in batched and unbatched cases (see tests) based on the par_map\r\n\r\n\r\nThe philosophy of this PR is as followsL\r\n\r\nIt does three things\r\n\r\n* introduce paramviewer (see below)\r\n* adapt combined modifiers to use paramviewer\r\n* adapt constraints to use paramviewer\r\n\r\nfor those things some minor changes are done elsewhere\r\n\r\n* add tile method to tensor backends (PR #538)\r\n* adapt pdf.py to constrain API homogenization (scalar return values)\r\n* adapt paramset.py to work with batched constraints\r\n\r\nFinally to make sure we do things correctly I added\r\n* a lot of new tests\r\n\r\n\r\n---------\r\n\r\n\r\nIn order to be fast these constraint codes used to pre-compute indices into the parameter vector in order to quickly grab all the parameter values needed to compute the constraint term\r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n\r\n```\r\npar vector [ . . . . . x x x x . . . x . . . x x x x . . . . . x x ]\r\n```\r\n\r\nhere the `x` denote parameters which are constrained by a normal (or poisson), the param_set `slice` attribute denoted exactly where these are in the order defined in the pdf config.\r\n\r\nAn index vector, one could pass to `tensorlib.gather` in this case would be\r\n\r\n[ 6 7 8 9 13 17 18 19 20 26 27 ]\r\n\r\nto get \r\n\r\n```\r\n[ x x x x x x x x x x x ]\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen we moving to batch evaluation we suddenly do not have a single `(N,)` param vector but a parameter \"field\"\r\n\r\n```\r\npar field\r\n[ \r\n  [ . . . . . x x x x . . . x . . . x x x x . . . . . x x ],\r\n  [ . . . . . y y y y . . . y . . . y y y y . . . . . y y ],\r\n  [ . . . . . z z z z . . . z . . . z z z z . . . . . z z ],\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nso it's a bit harder to grab all these correctly. This is eventually done by the `acess_field` in the constraints, but the indices are computed (as before based on the param_set.slice attribute) using the `ParamViewer` helper class\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n(added by @kratsg with help from @lukasheinrich )\r\n\r\nA real world situation of what the batching is trying to achieve is to imagine a simple model. Let's say you have a single channel, two sample (signal + background) model with a constrained modifier, an uncorrelated bkg uncertainty (`bkg_shapesysN`), and an normalisation factor on the signal (parameter of interest, `mu_sig`). Imagine the channel has 4 bins, so we have:\r\n\r\n- one channel (4 bins)\r\n- two samples\r\n- 2 modifiers\r\n- 2 parameter sets (`parsets`)\r\n- 5 parameters (`mu_sig, bkg_shapesys1, bkg_shapesys2, bkg_shapesys3, bkg_shapesys4`)\r\n\r\nThe data space is 4 bin counts (plus 4 aux data for the `bkg_shapesysN`), so when evaluating\r\n\r\n```\r\n# (8,) + (5,) -> (1,)\r\nmodel.logpdf(pars, data)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `data` is `(8,)` tensor and `pars`  is a `(5, )` tensor. This PR allows us to *batch in parameter sets* which means evaluating multiple instances of parameter sets:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# (8,) + (B, 5) -> (B, 1)\r\nmodel.logpdf(pars, data)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat this PR does is to enable moving to more parameter sets (`B = batch_size`) but we do not enable batching just yet. The groundwork is laid in place for a future PR.\r\n\r\n# Checklist Before Requesting Reviewer\r\n\r\n- [x] Tests are passing\r\n- [x] \"WIP\" removed from the title of the pull request\r\n- [x] Selected an Assignee for the PR to be responsible for the log summary\r\n\r\n# Before Merging\r\n\r\nFor the PR Assignees:\r\n\r\n- [x] Summarize commit messages into a comprehensive review of the PR\r\n\r\n```\r\n* Add batched computation of constraints and modifiers \r\n* Add paramviewer class to handle selection of parameter subsets in batched regime\r\n* Add tests for paramviewer, batched combined modifiers, and batched combined constraints\r\n```", "created_at": "2019-07-23T10:42:23Z", "updated_at": "2019-09-05T19:01:39Z", "closed_at": "2019-09-05T19:00:52Z", "merged_at": "2019-09-05T19:00:52Z", "merge_commit_sha": "673c1b6ead9c4c15b499f6a34402d8eec3240b7b", "assignees": [{"login": "lukasheinrich", "id": 2318083, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIzMTgwODM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2318083?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich", "html_url": "https://github.com/lukasheinrich", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/followers", "following_url": "https://ap